Popular Port Harcourt-based artiste, Duncan Mighty, has announced that he is hale and hearty. He was involved in a ghastly motor accident on January 2. He took to his verified Instagram to share the good news with his fans. He wrote in a mix of English and pidgin: “God Bless you all for your prayers.   Southeast schools must sing Biafran anthem, IPOB threatens     Retired soldiers demand 24 months pension arrears     Buhari replaces Ararume with Okadigbo as NNPC board chair   - Advertisement - “On the 2nd January, on our way to Uyo, our vehicle drove straight into the river after the brake of a trailer on a high speed failed. “It was the last thing I could remember. “Next thing is seeing myself in a hospital. God made no be man-made. “To our rescuers, Akwa Ibom/ Ogoni youths God bless you more and more. “I’ve been discharged and sound. “Na today I get another phone I say make I cassette the good news.”